Use : boot-img.sh [OPTIONS]
boot from a qcow image
this is a wrapper of the qemu utilitie.

Mandatory:
--image(-i) IMG		name of the image to create

Other:
--help (-h)		this help message
--memory (-m) RAM	ram allocated to the virtual machine
--cdrom (-c) CDROM	cdrom drive
--boot (-b) BOOT	boot drive
			a	floppy
			c	hard drive
			d	cdrom drive
			n	ethernet
